WEBVTT

00:02.569 --> 00:04.970
When I get nervous,
I have a little bit
of a drinking problem.

00:04.971 --> 00:06.672
           I have never seen you
                   sober.

00:06.674 --> 00:08.574
            Whitney:
  This is not "under control."

00:08.576 --> 00:10.976
     This is the definition
      of <i> "out</i> of control"!

00:10.978 --> 00:12.845
     [Retching]

00:12.847 --> 00:16.415
    You really think our actions
              are meaningless?

00:17.385 --> 00:18.684
                 [Screaming]

00:18.686 --> 00:20.352
      Oh, shit!

00:20.354 --> 00:23.322
        When you're really ready
     to go down the rabbit hole,

00:23.324 --> 00:24.923
                  call me.

00:26.192 --> 00:28.027
     [Dog barks in distance]

00:28.029 --> 00:29.695
     [Nicole clears throat,
         bottle clinks]

00:29.697 --> 00:34.133
   [Indistinct conversations]

00:35.503 --> 00:36.502
                    Hey.

00:36.504 --> 00:38.103
             You have chlamydia.

00:38.105 --> 00:39.338
        What?

00:39.340 --> 00:40.873
                   I said,
           "You have chlamydia."

00:40.875 --> 00:42.441
  How do you know?

00:42.443 --> 00:45.310
       Because you rawdogged me.
           And I have chlamydia.

00:46.714 --> 00:48.614
     Excellent.

00:50.017 --> 00:51.884
     [Grunts]
                 Your place
              is kind of gross.

00:51.886 --> 00:54.920
  Well, gee, I'm --
I'm real embarrassed about that,

00:54.922 --> 00:57.089
 uh, woman who just
 gave me chlamydia.

00:57.091 --> 00:59.258
  Normally, I have
a surprisingly tidy,

00:59.260 --> 01:00.592
young black man come in

01:00.594 --> 01:02.561
and clean up after me,
     but, um...

01:02.563 --> 01:04.263
    [Smacks lips]

01:04.265 --> 01:06.532
You know, I realize that just
sounded like he was my servant.

01:06.534 --> 01:08.634
He's not my servant.

01:08.636 --> 01:10.636
 Also just realized
that it sounded like

01:10.638 --> 01:12.805
  I'd be surprised
that a black man was tidy.

01:12.807 --> 01:14.706
  You know, I think
I'm at my most problematic

01:14.708 --> 01:15.908
   before I've had
     my coffee.

01:15.910 --> 01:17.810
                    Yeah.
     What are you talking about?

01:17.812 --> 01:20.779
  [Toilet flushes in distance]
That's a good question.
       [Sighs]

01:20.781 --> 01:22.748
My roommate recently
  moved out on me,

01:22.750 --> 01:24.817
and I'm still adjusting
      to that.

01:24.819 --> 01:27.219
      You know?
Doing pretty well overall.

01:27.221 --> 01:30.155
     Did I shit
over there in that corner?

01:30.157 --> 01:31.723
                     No.
               That was Rick.

01:31.725 --> 01:33.392
         Oh.

01:33.394 --> 01:35.094
     Seems like
a very nice young man.

01:35.096 --> 01:38.664
Oh, you have syphilis.
   You're welcome.

01:38.666 --> 01:39.965
Maybe Rick does, too.

01:39.967 --> 01:41.166
  I don't remember
 every little thing

01:41.168 --> 01:42.267
 that happened here
     last night.

01:42.269 --> 01:43.735
      [Grunts]

01:43.737 --> 01:45.737
                   I think
               it's infected.

01:45.739 --> 01:47.139
        What?

01:47.141 --> 01:49.308
                    That.
       Shit.

01:49.310 --> 01:51.009
  The hell is that?

01:51.011 --> 01:55.681
              It's two lizards
              69ing each other.

01:55.683 --> 01:58.250
        Well,
that's less than ideal.

01:58.252 --> 01:59.251
      Oh, boy.

01:59.253 --> 02:02.788
      Damn it.
        Man.

02:06.360 --> 02:07.392
                     Oh.

02:09.630 --> 02:12.931
        Does anyone know
 where this guy keeps his drugs?

02:12.933 --> 02:15.467
  [Muffled, indistinct chatter]

02:18.339 --> 02:19.805
   [Monitor beeping steadily]

02:19.807 --> 02:21.707
              Hey.
               Hi.

02:21.709 --> 02:22.808
         Oh,
   Mr. Brockmire.

02:22.810 --> 02:24.343
   Oh, I hope you don't mind.

02:24.345 --> 02:26.545
     My students were hoping
           to observe.

02:26.547 --> 02:29.515
   It's not every day they get
    to see a case like this.

02:29.517 --> 02:30.883
                    What,
      you mean like a celebrity?

02:30.885 --> 02:32.217
        Sure.

02:32.219 --> 02:34.219
                 Yeah, hey,
       more, the merrier, right?

02:34.221 --> 02:36.388
        It might help us
    if you could just take us

02:36.390 --> 02:37.956
             through
       the last few weeks.

02:37.958 --> 02:40.058
                    Well,
            best I can remember,

02:40.060 --> 02:42.027
      I threw away my dream job,

02:42.029 --> 02:43.462
              and then I became
               the focal point

02:43.464 --> 02:45.731
     for a national conversation
                 about race.

02:45.733 --> 02:47.166
     Oh, right.

02:47.168 --> 02:48.834
                    Yeah.
             Yeah, I'm that guy.

02:48.836 --> 02:50.636
               Just, you know,
              out of curiosity,

02:50.638 --> 02:53.372
               how many of you
     are on my side in all that?

02:54.708 --> 02:56.475
                  Alright.
                  One, two.

02:56.477 --> 02:59.711
      And how many of you are on
  that racist Art Newlie's side?

03:01.682 --> 03:03.549
                  Really?!
                    Wow.

03:03.551 --> 03:05.517
             I mean, I know this
    is the South and everything,

03:05.519 --> 03:08.153
              but y'all, you're
              highly educated
              medical doctors.

03:08.155 --> 03:10.155
             You're not ashamed
        to admit that in public?

03:10.157 --> 03:11.190
                   Well...

03:11.192 --> 03:12.824
         Let's get back
             to you.

03:12.826 --> 03:16.862
    Well, I have definitely been
      in a cycle of blacking out

03:16.864 --> 03:19.264
                and waking up
  in very strange places lately.

03:19.266 --> 03:20.566
              Recently came to

03:20.568 --> 03:23.101
               at a strip club
             as it was closing.

03:23.103 --> 03:25.037
              It wasn't late --
       just the health inspector

03:25.039 --> 03:26.772
                had walked in
        and shut the place down.

03:26.774 --> 03:29.007
                 After that,
            I remember waking up

03:29.009 --> 03:32.044
            next to a young lady
       with very few inhibitions

03:32.046 --> 03:33.712
               and quite a lot
                of chlamydia.

03:33.714 --> 03:36.114
                 But, well,
  you probably know that, right?

03:36.116 --> 03:37.616
              You got my chart
                right there.

03:37.618 --> 03:40.185
You -- You actually have
two strains of chlamydia --

03:40.187 --> 03:42.621
  one on your penis
and one in your throat.

03:42.623 --> 03:46.725
       Is that what I'm tasting?
   Oh, Rick, you sneaky bastard.

03:46.727 --> 03:48.260
              Well,
  you also have liver damage...

03:48.262 --> 03:51.129
                       Ugh.
     ...blunt-force trauma,
           and scurvy,

03:51.131 --> 03:53.198
        which is actually
       why we're all here.

03:53.200 --> 03:55.734
      This is the only case
      we'll ever get to see

03:55.736 --> 03:57.035
     outside of a textbook.

03:57.037 --> 03:58.971
                Scurvy, huh?

03:58.973 --> 04:01.106
             It's that why my --
     my teeth are getting loose?

04:01.108 --> 04:04.042
  I was just hoping that my gums
     were getting more flexible.

04:04.044 --> 04:08.213
             Well, I always have
        referred to orange juice

04:08.215 --> 04:12.251
     as a glass of vodka wasted,
                  so, uh...

04:12.253 --> 04:14.386
               I guess scurvy
                makes sense.

04:14.388 --> 04:16.521
        [Telephone rings]

04:19.827 --> 04:21.226
              Can I talk to you
                  a minute?

04:21.228 --> 04:22.794
        Yeah.

04:22.796 --> 04:24.630
   So, what is your relationship
              with the patient?

04:24.632 --> 04:27.766
                  His, uh,
            ex-business partner.

04:27.768 --> 04:29.001
            You didn't have that
                on the thing,

04:29.003 --> 04:30.569
          so I just wrote it in.

04:30.571 --> 04:31.837
     Don't worry. I'll make sure
             he gets home safe.

04:31.839 --> 04:32.971
     No, no, no,
     no, no, no.

04:32.973 --> 04:34.172
    He shouldn't
 be going anywhere,

04:34.174 --> 04:35.641
not in his condition.

04:35.643 --> 04:37.476
          What's wrong with him,
                  exactly?

04:37.478 --> 04:39.278
      Honestly?
     Everything.

04:39.280 --> 04:41.980
His body is literally
   shutting down,

04:41.982 --> 04:45.250
and if your friend does not
stop drinking, and soon,

04:45.252 --> 04:46.418
     your friend
    is gonna die.

04:46.420 --> 04:48.520
                I should not
            have left him alone.

04:48.522 --> 04:50.956
                    Okay.
   I'll take care of everything.

04:50.958 --> 04:54.092
               I'll make sure
   he does not leave my...sight.

04:54.094 --> 04:56.094
                        [Sighs]

04:56.096 --> 04:57.963
          Have you seen
     a bottle of champagne?

04:57.965 --> 04:59.631
  The old man next door swears
      that he brought it in

04:59.633 --> 05:00.932
          to celebrate
        his new grandson.

05:00.934 --> 05:02.100
       [P.A. system beeps]

05:02.102 --> 05:03.435
  Man: <i> Doctor on call, dial ER.</i>

05:03.437 --> 05:05.971
    <i> Doctor on call, dial ER.</i>

05:05.973 --> 05:09.975
      Well, I want to thank
    everyone for being here.

05:09.977 --> 05:13.478
 Jean, you have some experience
  with interventions 'cause...

05:13.480 --> 05:15.447
         -Because I was
         a filthy drunk.

05:15.449 --> 05:17.449
           It's okay.
         You can say it.

05:17.451 --> 05:20.118
 Nature and nurture both pushed
 me and Jim towards the bottle,

05:20.120 --> 05:21.820
         but now, I have
     the tools to help him.

05:21.822 --> 05:24.122
         -What made you
        get sober, Jean?

05:24.124 --> 05:25.624
      -At my intervention,

05:25.626 --> 05:27.492
  when it was my husband Norm's
         turn to speak,

05:27.494 --> 05:30.195
            he said,
      "Stop, Jean, please."

05:30.197 --> 05:32.964
   Now, Norm doesn't normally
       carry on like that,

05:32.966 --> 05:34.466
    so it cut me to the bone.

05:34.468 --> 05:36.535
             I'm really nervous,
                  you guys.

05:36.537 --> 05:39.538
       Jim is so good at turning
        an argument against you.

05:39.540 --> 05:40.972
          -[Scoffs]
          -Word.
          -That's true.

05:40.974 --> 05:42.974
              I once apologized

05:42.976 --> 05:45.377
              for the skidmarks
              on his underwear.

05:45.379 --> 05:48.513
    That's why I had each of you
    write a letter to read from,

05:48.515 --> 05:50.082
                 so it isn't
               a conversation.

05:50.084 --> 05:51.650
               You get to say
         everything you need to.

05:51.652 --> 05:55.153
        Now, I suggest you start
      with an "I feel" sentence.

05:55.155 --> 05:56.855
           Okay, okay.

05:56.857 --> 06:00.425
    I feel like there's a lot
 of love in this room right now.

06:00.427 --> 06:03.995
        No, start with something
   that's not quite that stupid.

06:03.997 --> 06:05.230
                 Okay, guys.
    You know, it's almost 11:00.

06:05.232 --> 06:06.398
            We should really go.

06:06.400 --> 06:08.400
            Actually,
    we shouldn't go anywhere.

06:08.402 --> 06:11.603
       Three...two...one.

06:11.605 --> 06:13.705
          [Door opens]

06:13.707 --> 06:15.907
        Jack, my friend,
  give me a lunchtime special.

06:15.909 --> 06:17.376
 Why don't you make it a double?

06:17.378 --> 06:19.711
    Throw it on the rocks --
     little change of pace.

06:19.713 --> 06:21.079
        Jim.

06:21.081 --> 06:22.114
                  Charles.

06:25.252 --> 06:27.619
                   This is
              an intervention.

06:27.621 --> 06:30.789
                Oh, Charles,
       you clever, little S.O.B.

06:30.791 --> 06:33.225
                My goodness.
              Look at you all.

06:33.227 --> 06:35.394
         Guess I'm trapped, huh?

06:35.396 --> 06:37.696
            No sense chewing off
              my own leg here.

06:37.698 --> 06:39.030
                 [Chuckles]

06:39.032 --> 06:40.432
                 Who knows?

06:40.434 --> 06:42.367
           Maybe the eighth time
             will be the charm.

06:43.498 --> 06:46.133
      [Chuckling] Oh, boy.
       Well, I got to say.

06:46.135 --> 06:49.036
   Seeing y'all come together
  like this, trying to save me

06:49.038 --> 06:52.906
from the self-destructive spiral
      that I'm in, it's --

06:52.908 --> 06:54.041
        I'm underwhelmed.

06:54.043 --> 06:55.742
Oh, come on, Jim!
       Jim.

06:55.744 --> 06:57.244
        I'm just saying,
         when they throw

06:57.246 --> 06:58.312
     an intervention for you
