    if you don't.

08:43.686 --> 08:45.252
             Learn how to accept
               a favor, okay?

08:45.254 --> 08:46.486
 Just -- Just --
                    Okay?

08:46.488 --> 08:48.055
                 Thank you.

08:48.057 --> 08:50.257
             Gonna have a bagel.

08:50.259 --> 08:52.859
        No cream cheese? Really?
              Are you kidding?

08:52.861 --> 08:56.763
       Alright. I'll eat it dry.
        Tastes like a Nerf ball.

08:56.765 --> 08:58.498
                   [Sighs]

08:59.455 --> 09:00.955
        Lucy,
you want to start us off?

09:00.957 --> 09:02.857
         [Sighing] Okay.

09:02.859 --> 09:04.759
            Hi, Jim.

09:04.761 --> 09:05.760
      [Chuckles nervously]

09:05.762 --> 09:09.297
            This is really hard.

09:09.299 --> 09:12.267
           I'm here today to say
                 I love you.

09:12.269 --> 09:14.469
     Well, thank you, Lucy.

09:14.471 --> 09:17.305
    You know, I-I hear that,
     and-- and I accept it.

09:17.307 --> 09:19.474
         That means a lot to me.

09:19.476 --> 09:21.142
            But I also came here
                 to tell you

09:21.144 --> 09:23.144
   how your drinking has hurt me
          in the following ways.

09:23.146 --> 09:26.414
  Nope. I hurt you? Excuse me.
 I hurt <i> you?</i> Are you kidding me?

09:26.416 --> 09:28.116
  'Cause you know what hurt me?

09:28.118 --> 09:30.151
  No, when you were dildo-deep
   in our neighbor's asshole.

09:30.153 --> 09:32.487
     Jim!
         Little too much?
         I do apologize.

09:32.489 --> 09:34.289
           I'm sorry.
         Intervene away.

09:34.291 --> 09:37.559
   We would end up
at the stripper's houseboat

09:37.561 --> 09:40.161
   drinking mezcal
   from her shoe.

09:40.163 --> 09:43.298
  [Chuckles] It was
the best night of my life!

09:43.300 --> 09:45.266
      [Laughs]

09:47.637 --> 09:51.005
  Uh, I think Uribe
   did this wrong.

09:51.007 --> 09:52.574
            [Scoffs]

09:52.576 --> 09:58.947
    3,426 days --
that's how long I've been sober.

09:58.949 --> 10:02.617
Each day is just as hard
as the last, maybe harder.

10:02.619 --> 10:05.019
Every day, a part of me wants
   to drink again.

10:05.021 --> 10:07.622
   Every morning,
I wake up and I wonder,

10:07.624 --> 10:10.325
"Today, will I embrace
     step seven

10:10.327 --> 10:13.661
  and ask for help
to overcome my shortcomings,

10:13.663 --> 10:16.464
   or will I kiss
my miserable children goodbye,

10:16.466 --> 10:19.000
lock myself in the garage,
and take down 40 ounces

10:19.002 --> 10:21.536
 of drug-store vodka
   before lunch?"

10:21.538 --> 10:24.372
                     ♪♪

10:24.374 --> 10:27.108
I can almost taste it.

10:27.110 --> 10:30.211
                     ♪♪

10:30.213 --> 10:32.313
           Hey, guys.
     I hope you don't mind.

10:32.315 --> 10:34.516
       I had them put mine
        in teleprompter.

10:34.518 --> 10:38.453
    Eye contact is how I tend
  to connect with my audience.

10:38.455 --> 10:40.021
         Jim, I thought
       it only appropriate

10:40.023 --> 10:42.957
      to start with a quote
   by the great Maya Angelou.

10:42.959 --> 10:45.326
  "Love recognizes no barriers.

10:45.328 --> 10:46.995
        It jumps hurdles,

10:46.997 --> 10:48.329
        it leaps fence--"

10:48.331 --> 10:50.198
               Anybody object
          to me putting a bullet

10:50.200 --> 10:52.133
         in the head of whatever
  the hell that was about to be?

10:52.135 --> 10:53.201
          Together: No.

10:53.203 --> 10:55.136
   Jim, you've been a mentor,

10:55.138 --> 10:59.174
   a hero, a rival, a friend.

10:59.176 --> 11:02.677
       But through it all,
     there's been one thing

11:02.679 --> 11:06.714
       that I have really,
  really wanted to say to you.

11:06.716 --> 11:09.150
                     ♪♪

11:09.152 --> 11:11.319
    Milwaukee just hired me.

11:11.321 --> 11:13.488
         [Paper rustles]

11:13.490 --> 11:18.393
            Fuck you,
      you goddamn vampire,

11:18.395 --> 11:20.261
      you wrinkly has-been!

11:20.263 --> 11:22.897
I'm a Major League broadcaster!"

11:22.899 --> 11:25.233
            [Growls]

11:29.439 --> 11:33.408
                  [Laughs]

11:33.410 --> 11:35.910
            [Laughs]
              Hey?

11:35.912 --> 11:38.413
                 Holy shit,
             that's a good bit.

11:38.415 --> 11:40.048
                   Damn it, Raj.
            Yes. Yes.

11:40.050 --> 11:42.283
       [Chuckling] I didn't know
            you had that in you.

11:42.285 --> 11:43.751
                  Oh, man.
                Look at that.

11:43.753 --> 11:45.887
 You did win me over in the end.
                Good for you.

11:45.889 --> 11:48.890
 I told you I would.
